        "mode": "runOnceForEachItem",
        "jsCode": "const ticketId = $('Postgres - Fetch Tickets').item.json.ticket_id;\nconst comments = $('HTTP - Fetch Ticket Comments KBGap').item.json.comments || [];\n\nconst publicComments = comments\n  .filter(c => c.public)\n  .slice(0, 3)\n  .map(c => c.body || '')\n  .join('\\n\\n---\\n\\n')\n  .slice(0, 2000);\n\nreturn {\n  json: {\n    ticket_id: ticketId,\n    article_linked_flag: $('Postgres - Fetch Tickets').item.json.article_linked_flag,\n    status: null,\n    form_id: 1260812421569,\n    system_prompt: `You are a support ticket analyzer. Extract the core support question from the ticket below. Remove all personally identifiable information (names, emails, phone numbers, account numbers, dates of birth, facility names). Return only a 2-3 sentence plain English summary of the technical or functional issue being reported. No PHI, no metadata, just the question.`,\n    user_prompt: `Conversation:\\n${publicComments || 'No comments available'}`\n  }\n};\n"
